item.title: Confused
item.dc:creator: @Teem_Rocket Teem_Rocket
item.description:
@Teem_Rocket wrote:

That’s a Bracket error. 100 errors being thrown doesn’t always mean It’s a Bracket error, but in this case it is. For example, if you forget to include a core import, you could have well over 100 errors depending on class size and references. Even though the maximum errors displayed in your prompt will be 100.

Anyway…

Post the piece(s) of code you were working with and detail what you’ve edited.

P.S. That user was referring to utilizing an Integrated Developmental Environment. This is a sort of program that is designed specifically for programming and can help with what you’re doing. They have several helpful features, but can be a bit overwhelming for a newbie (no offense of course). If you’re interested in trying out an I.D.E (which can tell you about your Brackets), then try:

Eclipse I.D.E. for Java

IntelliJ I.D.E. for Java
